  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Indonesia Climate Adaptation and Disaster Resilience (CADRE)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Local Government Workers, Community Members, Farmers</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PCI is implementing a three-year CADRE program funded by USAID to strengthen the resilience of vulnerable rural populations in the Bengkulu Province to disaster and climate change. The main objectives are to strengthen institutional capacity for disaster and climate change management, reduce exposure and vulnerability through adapted livelihoods, and improve disaster preparedness practices of communities through knowledge and education. CADRE has formed Community Disaster Risk Reduction Committees to map their community and redesign them for disasters, educated the community how to respond to disasters, and encouraged disaster-resilient farming methods.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthen Institutional Capacities, Promote Adapted Livelihoods, Community Engagement, Government Agency Collaboration, Community Education, Mapping, Implementation of Community Action Plans, Training and Advocacy</narrative>
